Ad Text:
Head of Generative AI Execution

Our client, a leading financial services business, is seeking a highly experienced and dynamic Generative AI Execution Leader to spearhead the build, adoption and execution of Generative AI and Agentic AI technologies across specific business functions.

This role will combine technical architecture expertise with product strategy. The post holder will be accountable for driving the identification, evaluation, and implementation of high value AI use cases. The ability to balance deep technical expertise and business acumen while ensuring rigorous adherence to regulatory and ethical standards is essential for this business-critical hire.

Responsibilities

Strategic Leadership: Own the end-to-end GenAI strategy and roadmap. Partner with business units to identify, prioritise, and drive the execution of high-value AI use cases with clear ROI frameworks.
Technical Expertise: Build high-performance AI infrastructure, for LLM evaluation and fine-tuning. Design and implement ML Operations (MLOps) frameworks and platforms at enterprise scale. Design cloud-based AI architectures on Azure, AWS, or similar platforms.
Architecture & Infrastructure: Collaborate closely with the Data Platform team to design and implement a secure, compliant, and highly scalable AI infrastructure. Establish a GenAI architecture competency within the Group framework.
Governance & Stakeholder Management: Present strategic technology assessments and to senior executives. Effectively communicate complex technical concepts, manage product risk, ensure regulatory compliance, and influence stakeholders across organisational boundaries to foster necessary partnerships.

Essential Capabilities

Deep expertise in building high-performance AI infrastructure for LLM evaluation and fine tuning.
Proven track record designing and implementing robust MLOps frameworks and platforms at enterprise scale.
Experience in designing cloud-based AI architectures on platforms like Azure or AWS.
Strong understanding of current GenAI capabilities and emerging AI technologies.

Business Acumen

Ability to create and convey a compelling vision to key stakeholders and cross-functional teams.
Strategic mindset with the ability to balance innovation with practical implementation and strong market analysis capabilities.
A test and learn mindset and a proven track record of evidence-based decision-making.

Prior Experience

Significant technical experience in complex project, program, portfolio, or delivery management roles.
Previous experience in roles specifically focused on high-impact AI/ML implementations.
Demonstrated experience designing and implementing AI platforms or large-scale data transformation initiatives.
Proven track record of successful enterprise technology delivery at scale within highly regulated industries, ideally in banking and financial services.

Should you have the ability to create scalable AI infrastructure for model evaluation and deployment and can implement GenAI architecture competency please apply below or contact Graham Walker on 0417 630 485 or email your details gwalker@welovesalt.com to discuss further.

Job Title: Senior Software Engineer, Geo, Urban Mobility
Ad Text:
At Google, we have a vision of empowerment and equitable opportunity for all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and commit to building reconciliation through Google’s technology, platforms and people and we welcome Indigenous applicants. Please see our Reconciliation Action Plan for more information.

Minimum qualifications:

Bachelor’s degree or equivalent practical experience.
5 years of experience with software development in one or more programming languages.
3 years of experience in testing, maintaining, or launching software products, and 1 year of experience with software design and architecture.
3 years of experience with applied data science and statistical methods, machine learning (ML) algorithms and tools, or applied ML (e.g., deep learning, natural language processing, Large Language Model).
Preferred qualifications:

PhD in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics or a related field.
5 years of experience with data structures/algorithms.
1 year of experience in a technical leadership role.
Experience in routing algorithms.
Knowledge of mathematics and statistical methods.
About the job


Google's software engineers develop the next-generation technologies that change how billions of users connect, explore, and interact with information and one another. Our products need to handle information at massive scale, and extend well beyond web search. We're looking for engineers who bring fresh ideas from all areas, including information retrieval, distributed computing, large-scale system design, networking and data storage, security, artificial intelligence, natural language processing, UI design and mobile; the list goes on and is growing every day. As a software engineer, you will work on a specific project critical to Google’s needs with opportunities to switch teams and projects as you and our fast-paced business grow and evolve. We need our engineers to be versatile, display leadership qualities and be enthusiastic to take on new problems across the full-stack as we continue to push technology forward.

The Geo team is focused on building the most accurate, comprehensive, and useful maps for our users, through products like Maps, Earth, Street View, Google Maps Platform, and more. Every month, more than a billion people rely on Maps services to explore the world and navigate their daily lives.

The Geo team also enables developers to use the power of Google Maps platforms to enhance their apps and websites. As they plot a course for the future of mapping, they are solving complex computer science problems, designing beautiful and intuitive product experiences, and improving our understanding of the real world.

Responsibilities

Write and test product or system development code.
Participate in, or lead design reviews with peers and stakeholders to decide amongst available technologies.
Review code developed by other developers and provide feedback to ensure best practices (e.g., style guidelines, checking code in, accuracy, testability, and efficiency).
Contribute to existing documentation or educational content and adapt content based on product/program updates and user feedback.
Triage product or system issues and debug/track/resolve by analyzing the sources of issues and the impact on hardware, network, or service operations and quality.
